  "body": "​\r\n\r\nHey Will,\r\n\r\nEnrollment for the AI Consultancy Project – our program for you\r\nto engineer ROI with AI using our PROOF Process™ for consultants\r\nand owner-operators – closes tonight at 11:59 PM Pacific.\r\n\r\nThis is the last email I’ll send about joining the program for\r\nthis cohort. If you know the timing isn’t right for you, that’s\r\nokay – IWAI will be here when you’re ready.\r\n\r\nIf something else is giving you a bit of pause, then I want you\r\nto know you're not alone…\r\n\r\n-------------------------------------------------\r\nStory Time: Me, 14 years ago in Washington, DC...\r\n-------------------------------------------------\r\n\r\nThe Rob you’re looking at there was making $50K per year as a\r\nsolo developer and lovestruck for the woman sitting next to him.\r\nThey didn’t have much - just a 1-bedroom apartment between the\r\ntwo of them and a daily routine.\r\n\r\nShe’d go off to work at a DC accounting firm.\r\nHe’d work remotely from the kitchen countertop.\r\n\r\nIt wasn’t much, and yet, I felt like I had it all. I knew she was\r\nthe one for me, and I was determined to create a life we’d always\r\nbe grateful for.\r\n\r\nAs for what that looked like…well, if anything, I had a much\r\nbetter idea of what I didn’t want:\r\n\r\n❌ 60-80+ hour work weeks that kept us apart.\r\n​\r\n❌ Saying no to vacations because I had to \"put in extra weekend\r\nwork.\"\r\n​\r\n❌ To become an “absent” dad and partner who, even when in the\r\nroom, was “away in his head at work.”\r\n​\r\n❌ Having zero time or energy to give back to the causes we cared\r\nabout.\r\n​\r\n❌ Scraping by to make ends meet, constantly stressed about what\r\ncame next.\r\n\r\nI was willing to do whatever it took to not end up like this.\r\n\r\nI wanted more.\r\n\r\nAnd after over a decade of ‘figuring it out’, I can say this…\r\n\r\n-------------------------------------------------------------\r\nNow: I have more time to date my wife (and hang with our son)\r\n-------------------------------------------------------------\r\n\r\nFast forward to today and life looks very different.\r\n\r\nMy smile is even wider than the first pic because hey, the love\r\nof my life became my wife, and we have a son who knows he’s loved\r\nby both his parents.\r\n\r\nThat dream life we envisioned in our first apartment?\r\n\r\nAfter years of choosing ‘the path less traveled’, it became a\r\nreality: I built a $2M/year service freedom business.\r\n\r\nOne that allows me to do things like:\r\n\r\n* Date my wife all over again at our old date spots\r\n* Take father-son trips to hangout with Pokémon in Japan\r\n* \"Bucket-list family trips\" to places like Antarctica\r\n\r\nI’m talking about the kind of freedom where I take my wife to\r\nrevisit all our old date spots, while taking my son to tour the\r\nSmithsonian museums, and capping it all off with a family beach\r\ntrip to Delaware.\r\n\r\nGreat times… and whenever I got back to my home office, there is\r\nNO mountain pile-up of work – my systems and team take care of\r\nit.\r\n\r\nEmail?\r\n\r\nDone in less than 1 hour.\r\n\r\nInstead of feeling chained to the chair on a Monday, I'm thankful\r\nfor everything that got done while I was away.\r\n\r\nLife is very different now.\r\n\r\nBack then, I made $50K a year and was $20,000 in credit-card\r\ndebt.\r\n\r\nThen, just 1 year later, I made $175K – that 3.5X jump happened\r\nbecause I decided to stop ‘fucking around with freelancing’ and\r\nfinally get serious.\r\n​\r\n(btw, all the client and consultancy skills + systems I built\r\nback then are all part of the Trusted Advisor Skills Engine™ - 14\r\nyears later, they’re still relevant, even with AI).\r\n\r\nIt's interesting… because I’ve had friends who were paid just as\r\nwell, even more so, but they rarely had all 4 freedoms...\r\n\r\n* Freedom of Time: Spend your days on things that matter—whether\r\nthat’s work, family, or exploring something new.\r\n* Freedom of Money: Build stability for yourself and your loved\r\nones while enjoying the life you’ve worked for.\r\n* Freedom of Relationships: Surround yourself with people who\r\nuplift you and align with your values.\r\n* Freedom of Purpose: Live a life that’s meaningful to you,\r\nwhether through your work, loved ones, or giving back.\r\n\r\nNow, after having done it, and repeatedly showing others to do\r\nit, I can confidently say I’ve found a timeless way to do it.\r\n\r\nInvesting in yourself.\r\nFinding the right mentor.\r\nCommitting to your goals.\r\n\r\nTo create lasting change in life, these things have always been\r\ntrue. Do it right, and a life of flexible freedom isn't some\r\npie-in-the-sky dream. It's doable so long as you're willing to\r\nput in the work.\r\n\r\nWhat's different now is The AI Economy – there’s even more\r\nopportunity…and also more risk for anyone without a clear way to\r\nengineer ROI with AI.\r\n\r\nSure, it'll still take work, but you’re no stranger to hard work.\r\nThe difference with this, is every hour of work you put into this\r\nis a step closer to more of the life you want.\r\n\r\nRealistically, expect to put in at least 5 hours a week. If that\r\nsounds doable, then I'm here to help you win. So is our team. And\r\nso is our 1,000+ and growing community of AI consultants and\r\nowner-operators.\r\n\r\nEnrollment for the AI Consultancy Project (\r\nhttps://innovatingwithai.com/ai-consultancy/?ck_subscriber_id=3998817959\r\n) closes tonight at 11:59 PM Pacific.\r\n\r\nJoin and we’ll work closely to create an AI consultancy that is\r\ndesigned for your freedom and flexibility. One where you become\r\nthe Trusted AI Advisor.\r\n\r\nThen, with enough momentum, you’ll be free to not just enjoy\r\nlife, but invest some of your time making this world a better\r\nplace than how you found it.\r\n\r\nYou got this,\r\n\r\n– Rob\r\nProud Dad at the Beach\r\n\r\n•••\r\n\r\n​ (\r\nhttps://innovatingwithai.com/ai-consultancy/?ck_subscriber_id=3998817959\r\n)Enrollment closes tonight at 11:59 PM PT\r\n\r\nThanks for reading! If you loved it, tell your friends to\r\nsubscribe.\r\n\r\nIf you didn’t enjoy the email you can unsubscribe here (\r\nhttps://01d6eb30.unsubscribe.kit-mail3.com/gkuvgemw68t5hlw40kdtrh8oddkpwsmh7940p\r\n).\r\n\r\nTo change your email or preferences manage your profile (\r\nhttps://preferences.kit-mail3.com/gkuvgemw68t5hlw40kdtrh8oddkpwsmh7940p\r\n).\r\n\r\n1580 N. Logan St., Suite 660, Denver, CO 80203\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\n​",
